\selectlanguage{english}
\begin{abstract}

Internet access is becoming increasingly popular. This can be explained by all the advantages offered by digital and precisely Internet. Among these advantages, it allows
companies to offer services to customers whatever they are. Based upon this advantage, we wanted to make available to the Beninese people, a web application allowing them to view and pay their bills from a web browser. This would essentially prevent the lost of time due to the long queues at the counter and to have easier access to their invoices. 

Despite all benifits from Internet, some drawbacks are known like cybercriminality, intrusion attempts into computer systems. Cybercrime is on the rise and intrusion attempts into computer systems is growing exponentially. With regard to these, several security measures must be taken in order to avoid as much as possible intrusions at the level of our application and the various servers. We therefore propose a secured architecture customized for the production of our application, which will be managed internally ( i.e. deployed within SBEE).

\paragraph{}
\textbf{Key words}: IT Security, Online Payment, Invoices, SBEE
\end{abstract}